    "en": {
      "title": "A reply from the cricket body to Arjuna's accusation",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lanka Cricket Institute has given an explanation regarding the statement made by Mr. Arjuna Ranatunga, the former minister and the current chairman of the Sports Council, that the sports council canceled a foreign trip planned by 7 officials of the Sri Lanka Cricket Institute by spending millions of money.",
        "The Cricket Institute states that Mr. Arjuna Ranatunga's statement is a false statement. Seven members of the Sri Lanka Cricket Board's executive committee were to join the ongoing Asia Cup as officials.",
        "The Cricket Institute also said that it had planned to discuss matters such as future match tours and the Ceylon Premier League with the Asian Cricket Council as well as with other countries.",
        "Also, it is further stated in the announcement issued by the cricket body that the cricket body will not use Sri Lankan government funds."
      ],
